snippet.textDisplay: Not to insult the channel or the effort that goes into these videos, because I love these videos and these guys' sense of humor, but to me the real meat of this channel has always been a group of entertaining friends sitting down at a computer and drawing something in photoshop. And I feel like that's not something that requires a lot of money or some super expensive recording studio or something. Hell, that's something I feel like I could do with my friends over the internet between shifts at my boring day job. So I just don't feel as worried as I would with something like collegehumor itself, which needed that expensive studio and a massive crew to make the skits they did. I feel like it'll work out for these guys.

I’m sad you felt you had to say sorry.
Can’t wait to support you in every artistic endeavour you take part in, including this channel while ever it’s sustainable and fun for you to do so and in any format/media you choose to expand in the future, that part hasn’t changed. I’m sorry for all the stress you must be feeling, nobody likes getting laid off. However insecure and scary it is, you can’t lose your talent like you can lose a job, keep being your lovely talented selves and someone will certainly pay you to exist, I wish youtube was financially stable my guys but let’s be real, you are fantastic and there will always be a religious audience of this format of art and comedy, listening to you while I work is what drives me to continue evolving and improving and it’s what convinced me there is worth in my artwork and makes my silly little ideas and drawings into characters I care about.
